dialogueText.dialogue:
 The writings are drawn, Sir, settlements made;   
'tis too 
late, Sir, and past all revocation.

 Nay, if he wo'not, I am ready to wait upon the     
Ladies; 
and I think I am the fitter Man.

 Come, come, here's a Gamester for you, let him 

be a little familiar sometimes; nay, what if a little rude; 
Gamesters may be rude with Ladies, you know.

 Come, pray Bud, let's go abroad before 'tis   
late;
for I will go, that's flat and plain.
